1 B. The State Board of Education shall adopt a program for the
2 career development of public school paraprofessionals. The purpose
3 of the program is to provide to public school paraprofessionals a
4 system of career development which is based upon education and
5 training advancement to encourage excellence among public school
6 paraprofessionals. Public school paraprofessionals who hold a
7 bachelor's degree in education or education studies and who have not
8 been out of the classroom for more than ten (10) years shall be
9 deemed to have satisfied any rule that requires additional
10 professional education coursework from an institution of higher
11 education under the adopted program. Nothing in this section shall
12 be construed to require public school paraprofessionals to
13 participate in the career development program.
14 C. The board of education of a school district shall have
15 authority to extend an existing contract with a public school
16 paraprofessional that provides for the payment of compensation for
17 paraprofessional services rendered for the same time period during
18 which the paraprofessional is also assigned to the school district
19 for practice teaching as a student teacher.
20 D. For the purposes of this section, a public school
21 paraprofessional is an employee of a school district whose position
22 is either instructional in nature, or who delivers other direct
23 services to students and/or their parents. A public school
24 paraprofessional serves in a position for which a teacher or another
