1 prof essional has the ultimate responsibility for the design,
2 implementation, and evaluation of the individual educational
3 programs or related services and student performance.
4 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-213 of Title 70, unless there
6 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 Teachers who hold a bachelor's degree in education or education
8 studies shall be deemed to have satisfied any State Board of
9 Education rule that requires teachers to complete additional
10 professional education coursework from an institution of higher
11 education as a condition to obtain, renew, or satisfy any other
12 professional development requirement for an emergency certificate,
13 alternate placement teaching certificate, or standard certificate if
14 the teacher has not been out of the classroom for more than ten (10)
15 years.
16 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
17 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
18 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
19 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
20 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
